Justice Minister Ronald Lamola has just announced that fees must fall activist Kanya Cekeshe qualifies for remission. The department is now looking at parole. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Justice Minister Ronald Lamola has just announced that Fees Must Fall activist Kanya Cekeshe qualifies for remission. President Cyril Ramaphosa will be granting a number of prisoner's remission. Ramaphosa made the announcement during his Reconciliation Day address in Bergville, KwaZulu Natal. READ: Ramaphosa grants special remission of sentence to prisoners Cekeshe is serving an eight-year prison sentence after he was convicted of public violence and malicious damage to property during the Fees Must Fall protests. He is one of the last Fees Must Fall activists still in prison. Lamaola says Cekeshe could be released as early as February 2020. “This means that he becomes eligible for parole immediately, he can then apply for those processes,” Lamola said.